added.title: The Code
added.description: Gumball learns the Wattersons have been stealing Mr. Robinson's wi-fi for years. When it goes down, they try and live without it but life offline proves too hard. Gumball and Darwin decide to hack their way through cyberspace to learn Mr Robinson's passcode.

added.title: The Bus
added.description: When Rocky suggests the Elmore Junior High kids skip school, the bus is boarded by criminals, who seem to want to teach them the importance of school attendance. The masked culprits are clearly the children's parents faking a heist to teach them a lesson. But when the police get involved for real, it becomes clear the parents aren't the ones pulling the strings.

added.title: The Slap
added.description: Tobias follows every single high-five with a butt-slap. So when Gumball doesn't get one, he feels insulted. He tries to get Tobias to slap his rear all day but when it doesn't work he decides they need some enforced one-on-one bro-time to build their relationship up to a butt-slap.

added.title: The Vacation
added.description: The Wattersons set off on a relaxing vacation and end up running for their lives! The Wattersons are swapping scary stories on a family vacation, when their car breaks down in the middle of the desert. They are left with no alternative but to trust a complete stranger, whose appearance matches the scary guy in Mom's story. When the stranger brings them to a derelict gas station, just as he did in mom's made-up scary story, the Wattersons can no longer pretend the story isn't coming true . . .

added.title: The Password
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are shocked to discover that Anais is Dad's favourite child. Mom has forced Dad to install a password on the computer. The pop-up clue advises them that the password is the name of Dad's favorite child. After trying "Gumball" and "Darwin" unsuccessfully, they discover the answer is, in fact, "Anais". They are determined to become Dad's favorites by any means necessary, even if it means undermining each other, plotting against Anais or driving a wedge between mom and dad . . .

added.title: The Mirror
added.description: When Gumball refuses to forward a scare email, the curse becomes all too real. Gumball receives a scare-email from a freaky ghost and decides to ignore it, despite Darwin's advice. He refuses to admit it, but the curse starts to come true and his whole family gets dragged into another dimension. Gumball and Darwin, with help from Carrie, set out to save their family.

added.title: The Limit
added.description: The Watterson family faces Mom's wrath in a supermarket.

added.title: The Plan
added.description: The Watterson kids come up with a fool-proof plan to save their mom, but is it Gumball-proof?

added.title: The Responsible
added.description: Gumball and Darwin babysit Anais "responsibly", whilst "irresponsibly" flooding the house.

added.title: The Mystery
added.description: Gumball sets out to solve the mystery of who stuffed Principal Brown into his locker.

added.title: The GI
added.description: Gumball and Darwin's martial arts costumes make them a laughing stock at school.

added.title: Storm in the Room
added.description: Steven goes into his room in the temple to look for answers.

added.title: Steven's Birthday
added.description: Steven has a birthday party out at the barn, and decides he has some growing up to do.

added.title: Mr. Greg
added.description: Steven, Greg and Pearl take a trip to Empire City to live the good life.

added.title: Garnet's Universe
added.description: Steven imagines what Garnet does with her day.

added.title: On the Run
added.description: Steven and Amethyst try out life on the road.

added.title: Classic Rock
added.description: Batman thinks he's helping a homeless old man who is being mugged on the street only to discover that the man is a powerful wizard being chased by demons in disguise. It turns out the wizard is on a mission to save Shazam from the clutches of Black Adam.

added.title: Night of the Bat
added.description: Superman and other Justice League members have to battle Batman when he gets possessed by an evil Djinn, Uthool, who is intent on using the JL power core to blow a crack in Earth.

added.title: Follow that Space Cab!
added.description: While Superman escorts his prisoner Mr. Mind between planets, he is attacked by Lobo who wants to collect a reward on Mind. Temporarily powered-down, Superman seeks Space Cabbie's help to get away from Lobo.

added.title: Zombie King
added.description: Grundy escapes his Louisiana prison intent on using a magical crystal which will allow him to raise the dead from their graves. Only Batman and Swamp thing stand in the way of his growing zombie army.

added.title: Time Share
added.description: Batman and Blue Beetle have to travel back in time to stop Chronos from destroying a young Dark Knight on his very first case.

added.title: Play Date
added.description: Toyman takes over the Justice League and turns them into avatars in a diabolical video game.

removed.title: Bubble Buddies
removed.description: Steven looks like a hero when he forms a magic crystal bubble around himself to protect a girl he likes from danger, but then panics when he can't figure out how to turn the bubble off!

removed.title: Crack the Whip
removed.description: Amethyst is left in charge of Steven and Connie, and there will be no training while she's around!

removed.title: Adventures in Light Distortion
removed.description: Steven and the Gems take off on a search and recovery mission.

removed.title: Message Received
removed.description: Steven has doubts about believing in everyone.

removed.title: Alone at Sea
removed.description: Steven and Greg take a boat trip out to sea and find themselves in dangerous water.

removed.title: Onion Gang
removed.description: Steven learns about Onion's secret group of friends.

removed.title: Joy Ride
removed.description: The Cool Kids help Steven put some fun back in his life.

removed.title: The New Lars
removed.description: Steven gets a new look into Lars' life.

removed.title: Rocknaldo
removed.description: Ronaldo sets out to find all the rock people living in Beach City!

removed.title: Party Animal
removed.description: Green Arrow, who is determined to finally throw a successful holiday party for the Justice League, finds his plans thwarted when Plastic Man brings a tranquilized super villain to the gathering.

removed.title: The Mustache
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin's wish comes true when they suddenly turn into men.

removed.title: The Origins
removed.description: When Mom and Dad struggle to keep hyperactive, toddler-aged Gumball from trashing the house and exhausting them, they decide to buy him a pet. It works, but there's a problem: every goldfish they get him is short-lived, and inevitably ends up being flushed down the toilet.

removed.title: The Fight
removed.description: Anais is convinced that Gumball is being bullied by Tina Rex.

removed.title: The Check
removed.description: Gumball, Darwin and Anais are delighted when Grandpa Louie gives them a check for $5000. They immediately start fantasizing over what to spend it on. But when Mom and Dad say they're going to spend the money on paying bills instead, it's a race to the bank to see who can cash the check first.

removed.title: The Sweaters
removed.description: Gumball and Darwin's reputation is challenged and they really couldn't care less...

removed.title: The World
removed.description: The amazing world of Elmore is full of inanimate objects that aren't nearly as inanimate as you might hope!

removed.title: The Traitor
removed.description: When Alan ditches Gumball to do something more fun, Gumball is desperate to track him down and make him pay for his betrayal.

removed.title: The Promise
removed.description: Darwin has promised to play video games with Gumball, but there is a Banana Joe-shaped problem...

removed.title: The Apprentice
removed.description: Gumball decides that the best way to prove to Mr. Fitzgerald that he's good enough for Penny is to become his apprentice for the day. The problem is Mr. Fitzgerald has an important interview and Gumball's enthusiastic attempts to help him might actually do more harm than good, both to Mr. Fitzgerald's business and to Gumball's future with Penny.

removed.title: The Girlfriend
removed.description: Jamie has decided she needs a sweetheart and, unlucky for him, she has decided Darwin is the best candidate.
